<HEADLINE> German Steel Giant Makes Double Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 12 (Xinhua) -- German steel giant Thyssen, which
is due to merge with its rival Krupp-Hoesch, today said it more
than doubled its profits during the financial 1996-1997 year
ending September 30.
</P>
<P>
The result was one of the best in history and the exact
figures would be released following board meeting at the end of
this month, the company said.
</P>
<P>
In the year 1995-1996, the heavy-industry sector achieved
profits of 610 million marks (359 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Thyssen said the sector turnover was set to top at 40 billion
marks in the financial 1996-1997, compared with 38.7 billion marks
for the previous corresponding period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
