<HEADLINE> Full Text of Li's Speech at Reception in Tokyo (Part One) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li
Peng, who is on a six-day official good-will visit to Japan,
delivered a speech here this afternoon at a welcoming reception
held by Japan-China friendship organizations. The full text of the
speech reads as follows:
Mr. Yoshio Sakurauchi,
Mr. Ikuma Dan,
Ladies, Gentlemen and Friends,
</P>
<P>
At this wonderful season, I feel greatly honored to be given
such a warm and grand reception and I am very glad to have an
opportunity to meet old and new friends who have always been
enthusiastic in promoting Sino-Japanese friendship. On behalf of
my wife and colleagues, I express my heartfelt gratitude to all
the friends here for your profound sentiments of friendship.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 25th anniversary of the normalization of
the Sino-Japanese diplomatic ties. And next year marks the 20th
anniversary of the signing of the China-Japan Treaty of Peace and
Friendship. Twenty-five years ago, leaders of the two countries
showed great foresight and made the wise decision to normalize
diplomatic ties between the two countries, which opened a new page
for Sino-Japanese relations. With the joint efforts made by the
two governments and the two peoples in the past 25 years, the
China-Japan relations and the cooperation and exchanges in all
areas between the two countries have scored remarkable
progress. This not only greatly benefited both China and Japan,
but contributed to peace and development in the Asia-Pacific
region and the world at large. The hard-earned development of
Sino-Japanese relations is an embodiment of the painstaking labor
and efforts made by people from several generations in the two
countries, including all the friends here. The Chinese and
Japanese peoples know the old saying, "When you drink water, think
of those who dug the well." Let us bear firmly in mind the
pioneers who work hard to normalize the diplomatic ties between
the two countries, and people from various circles who have been
making efforts to maintain and develop the Sino-Japanese friendly
ties. On behalf of the Chinese government and people, I avail
myself of this opportunity to renew to all Japan-China friendship
organizations and Japanese friends the assurances of my highest
consideration.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
