<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Books Berth for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia qualified for the
World Cup finals in France next summber after beating hosts Qatar
1-0 in the final match of the Asian Zone Group A qualifying
competition here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah S. Al Dosari scored the winner in the 63rd minute for
the visitors, who collected 14 points and automatically advanced
to France as the top finisher in the group.
</P>
<P>
Iran finished second with 12 points and will face group B
runner-up Japan in a play-off in a neutral venue on November 16.
</P>
<P>
The winner of that play-off will win a berth in France while
the loser meets Australia on an home-and-away format on November
22 and 29 for a place in the finals.
</P>
<P>
China, who edged the visiting Kuwait 1-0 in a meaningless clash
earlier in Dalian, China, came in third with 11 points, followed
by Qatar with 10 and Kuwait with eight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
