<HEADLINE> Russia Urges Iraq to Abide by UN Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Russia today asked Iraq to
immediately end the restrictions on the U.N. special commission
in charge of ridding Iraq of weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman Valery Nesterushkin was
quoted by the Interfax news agency as saying that if Iraq did so,
the U.N. Security Council would rule out the need of further
coordination between the member states on the tightening of
sanctions against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Russia's view on the issue is that Iraq must be given a
realistic prospect of overcoming its economic problems provided it
meets the demands of the international community, Nesterushkin
said.
</P>
<P>
He cautioned the Security Council should not take advantage of
the tense situation around Iraq to authorize any use of force
against it.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted the gravity of the situation around Iraq
should not be underestimated.
</P>
<P>
He finally called for the international community to come to an
understanding with Baghdad and persuade it to resume constructive
cooperation with UN special commission. 
</P>
