<HEADLINE> Full Text of Li's Speech at Reception in Tokyo (Part Four) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We hope the Japanese government and people will continue to
develop in the direction of peace despite obstructions. Only in
this way can Japan win understanding and respect in the world,
play a more active role in international affairs, and make greater
contribution to global peace and development.
Friends,
</P>
<P>
China is committing itself to building a modern socialism. The
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China held
recently summed up the success stories in the country's reform and
opening up, such as the ongoing endeavor to achieve modernization
for the past twenty years, defining Deng Xiaoping's Theory as our
guilding ideology, electing a new central leadership with Jiang
Zemin at the core, and drawing up the blueprint for China's future
development.
</P>
<P>
Our goal is to achieve basic modernization by the middle of the
next century. To achieve that we need to secure a long-term
peaceful international environment and maintain good relations
with surrounding countries. China is a staunch force safeguarding
world peace. China's development will pose no threat to any other
country. China will never seek hegemony even when it becomes
developed in the future. China upholds an independent foreign
policy of peace and attaches great importance to developing good
relations with surrounding countries.
</P>
<P>
It has been China's consistent policy to build and develop
long-term stable friendship and cooperation with Japan. I firmly
believe that a long-term stable good-neighborly relationship
between China and Japan will not only benefit our own peoples but
will also be conducive to world peace and human progress.
</P>
<P>
Thank you.
</P>
</TEXT>
