<HEADLINE> 5 Cypriot Ministers Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Five new ministers of the
Cypriot government were sworn in here today to replace the
ministers of the government's former coalition partner, who
resigned last week.
</P>
<P>
The five ministers were George Charalambides, George
Stavrinakis, Andreas Mantovanis, Efstathios Papadakis, Michalakis
Michaelides, who took the portfolio of defense; interior;
agriculture, natural resources and environment; labor and social
insurance; commerce, industry and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Five ministers of the center-right Democratic Party (DIKO)
resigned November 5 from the 11-member cabinet. But the reason for
the withdrawal of the party from the coalition government was not
made explicit.
</P>
<P>
Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides, 77, said last week he would
seek re-election in the presidential elections due February 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, 65-year-old Spyros Kyprianou, leader of DIKO and
Speaker of the House of Representative, also had decided to run
for the presidency and said that his party would exit from the
coalition if Clerides wanted to seek a second term.
</P>
<P>
Clerides, founder of the ruling rightwing Democratic Rally,
succeeded in the presidential election in February 1993 with the
support of the DIKO, which has five ministers in the cabinet.
</P>
</TEXT>
