<HEADLINE> Bahrain to Boycott Doha Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain today announced to
boycott the upcoming Middle East and North Africa economic
conference to be held in the Qatari capital Doha on November 16 to
18.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain's official Gulf News Agency quoted a senior official
in Bahrain's Forein Ministry as saying that Manama will not take
part in the conference in view of the deadlock in the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
The conference, which was traditionally attended by Arab
states, Israel and its major partners in the other part of the
world has been boycotted by most Arab countries due to Israel's
participation.
</P>
<P>
Egypt, Syria, the Palestinian Authority, Lebanon, the UAE,
Saudi Arabia and Morocco have voiced their boycott in protest
against Israel's failure of honoring peace agreements signed
with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Oman, Yemen, Jordan and Kuwait decided to take
part in the US-backed conference which has been downgraded from
a summit to the ministerial level. 
</P>
