<HEADLINE> Sakurauchi Calls For Enhancement of Sino-Japanese Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Japanese people should firmly
remember the great losses and sufferings China and other Asian
countries experienced due to the war launched by Japan and its
colonial rule, and look forward into the future enthusiastically.
</P>
<P>
These remarks were made by Chairman of the Japan Association
for the Promotion of International Trade Yoshio Sakurauchi here
today at a welcome reception held by seven Japan-China Friendship
organizations in honor of visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi said a long-term and stable cooperation with China
is indispensable to the sustainable and stable economic
development and cultural prosperity in Japan in such a world as is
witnessing great changes.
</P>
<P>
He said Japan and China took a historic step in the
normalization of their diplomatic ties 25 years ago and their
building of a new kind of friendly relationship thereafter.
</P>
<P>
Six years later, they concluded a treaty of peace and
friendship and promoted, to a significant extent, the exchanges
between the two countries in various areas such as politics,
economy, science and technology as well as culture and sports.
</P>
<P>
He attributed these achievements to the joint efforts of the
politicians and people of the older generation of the two
countries as well as the people present at today's reception.
</P>
<P>
He said the establishment of a firm relationship of mutual
trust between Japan and China and the strengthening of cooperation
between the two peoples in various fields oriented toward the 21st
century are also of vital importance to world peace and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Also at the reception, Chinese Premier Li proposed a five-point
principle governing the development of Sino-Japanese ties.
</P>
<P>
The seven organizations that co-hosted the welcome reception
were the Japan-China Friendship Association, Japan-China Society,
Japan-China Economic and Trade Association, Japan Association for
the Promotion of International Trade, Japan-China Cultural
Exchange Association, the Japanese Dietman's League for
Japan-China Friendship and Japan-China Friendship Center.
</P>
<P>
Present at the reception were more than 1,000 people from
various circles who have worked for the cause of Japan-China
friendship.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier arrived here yesterday afternoon for a
six-day official good-will visit to Japan. 
</P>
