<HEADLINE> Farmers Urged to Gather in Harvest Before </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian farmers
today were urged to gather in their harvest before an untimely
rain expected over the various parts of the country in the coming
ten days.
</P>
<P>
The call came from the National Meteorological Services Agency
of Ethiopia in a weather forecast here.
</P>
<P>
The agency said unseasonal rain is expected over the eastern,
central and northern parts of the country, adding that
agricultural experts should take the necessary measures to
protect the already harvested crops from disease and insects.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's grain production this year has been affected by
shortage of rainfall during the main rainy season from June to
September. According to an official announcement made last month,
about 4.6 million people were affected by drought and 420,000
metric tonnes of food is required to feed the victims. The
untimely rain will worsen the situation of food production this
year. 
</P>
