<HEADLINE> Middle East Peace Process Optimistic: Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Avivi Pinchas, the visiting
ambassador at the foreign office of Israel told Cameroon Tribune
today that he is optimistic over the middle east peace process,
adding that a concrete agreement for the future will be made.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Cameroon Tribune, ambassador Pinchas
noted that an agreement that will ensure the existence of
Palestinians and Israelis as neighbors is possible.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador reviewed that they are now talking of the
concrete agreement. "We did this with Egypt, the Camp David
Accord and i think we are ready to do the same with the
Palestinian people, " he said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador noted, "in the north of Israel, we are still
having problems with Lebanon and Syria. We are not saying the
south of Lebanon is part of Israel but we wish to have peace in
the northern part of Israel."
</P>
<P>
"Once Lebanon is able to ensure this peace," he continued,
"Israel will be ready to leave the area. Syria has an opportunity
to make peace with Israel. I am optimistic."
</P>
<P>
"Good neighbors will definately have some divisions. The
problem is to decide where the wall will be. But as regards
health, water supply etc., which require regional cooperation, we
have to work together," he added.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador also highlighted the good relations between
Israel and Cameroon. "Cameroon in the central African region and
Africa as a whole is one of the most friendly countries to
Israel," he said.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that during his visit, he met with Cameroonian
authorities to sample their views, "we have experince in
agro-industry and transport which we are ready to share."
</P>
<P>
The abassador announced that his ministry had decided to
nominate a new highly competent ambassador accredited to Cameroon
who will cover the sub-region in stead of the current charge
d'affair, "so as to improve ties between the two countries."
</P>
