national unity and brushing the current constitution aside are
not acceptable.
</P>
<P>
He accused the opposition parties of trying to achieve
privileges through dialgos.
</P>
<P>
The current government is elected by the Zambian people
democratically and therefore is a legitimate government, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sakala also said that Zambia's problems should be settled by
Zambians themselves and not by outsiders.
</P>
<P>
Zambians will build their own country here and not those
abroad, Sakala said.
</P>
<P>
