Arab countries that have announced their boycott of the
conference, namely, Egypt, Syria, the Palestinian National
Authority, Saudi Arabia, Morocco, the United Arab Emirates,
Lebanon, Sudan, Iraq, Libya and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
So far, in the 16 Arab countries which were invited, only
Jordan, Kuwait, Oman, Yemen and Tunisia have decided to show up.
</P>
<P>
The annual MENA conference, which has been held in Casablanca,
Amman and Cairo, was initiated in 1994 to integrate Israel into
the regional economy.
</P>
<P>
Arab countries have been split over whether or not to
attend the Doha conference as the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks
have ground to a virtual halt and the peace process on the
Lebanese and Syrian tracks have been on ice since 21 months ago.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian negotiating delegation led by its chief
delegate Saeb Erekat today briefed Meguid and Arab ambassadors on
the outcome of the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations in Washington,
which failed to touch the basic issues of the peace process.
</P>
