<P>
When launching the vaccination drive in the capital today,
Health Minister Charle Etoundi appealed to all parents with child
aged between zero to five to turn out massively and participate
in the exercise which is free of charge.
</P>
<P>
Vaccines have been channeled to all the 10 provinces in
Cameroun, medical officials told press today.
</P>
<P>
The eradication of poliomyelitis in the country by the year
2000 is a major objective set by the Camerounian government. To
achieve this goal, the Public Health Ministry instituted a
nationwide immunization campaign strategy known as the national
vaccination days.
</P>
<P>
The campaign will last six days but in two stages. The first
phase that started from today will last for three days while the
second phase will be on December 17-19, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Poliomyelitis is a disease which causes permanent or life
disabilities and leaves the child handicapped. The continent of
Africa has been observed as a vulnerable area for the spread of
the poliomyelitis virus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
