<HEADLINE> Switzerland Promoting Economic Ties With Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland held an economic
forum here today to promote its trade relations with Hong Kong
and its own image as a European partner for Asia.
</P>
<P>
Rolf Bodenmuller, consul-general of Switzerland in Hong Kong,
said: "We want to express our continuing strong confidence in the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) by organizing this
special Economic Forum of Switzerland."
</P>
<P>
The one-day forum, one of the key events in "Switzerland Greets
Hong Kong" promotion, is designed to promote links with Hong
Kong, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The forum covered a diverse range of subjects, including mutual
trade relations, and Switzerland as an investment location and
partner for Asian business.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland now is Hong Kong's sixth largest source of foreign
industrial investment, while Hong Kong ranks eighth as a
destination for Swiss exports. The city is the largest market for
Swiss watches, importing 490 million US dollars worth of
timepieces from that country in the first sixth months of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Klaus Jacobi, chairman of the Coordinating Commission for
the Presence of Switzerland Abroad, told the forum that he was
confident these strong economic and financial ties between Hong
Kong and Switzerland will be deepened and widened in the future.
</P>
<P>
In his speech entitled "Switzerland: a reliable European
partner for Asia," Professor Franz Blankart, Swiss Secretary of
State for Foreign Economic Affairs, expressed his wish that the
good partnership between his country and Asia will continue to
prosper into the next century.
</P>
<P>
About 18 percent of Swiss total exports are destined for Asian
markets and eight percent of the total imports come from the Asian
region.
</P>
<P>
The forum was jointly organized by the Swiss Office for Trade
Promotion OSEC, the Consulate General of Switzerland and the Hong
Kong General Chamber of Commerce.  
</P>
