<HEADLINE> Japan, China Agree on Environmental Protection Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 13 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan signed an
agreement here today on cooperating in environmental protection
oriented to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The agreement offered initiatives on selecting a pilot city
that is involved in environment-saving development, and improving
China's information networks on environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side recommended three cities: Northeast China's
Dalian, Central China's Guiyang and Southwest China's Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The relevant departments of the two governments will select one
of the three cities after a study by a 14-member joint board of
experts.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, members of the experts' board will
begin studying the initiatives and convene its first joint meeting
as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also said Japan will assist China in three years
to improve 100 information networks on environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached by Chinese and Japanese officials in
charge of economic and trade cooperation and environmental
protection during the ongoing official good-will visit of China's
Premier Li Peng. 
</P>
