<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of drivers and
maintenance workers from a Hong Kong bus company decided tonight
to call off their planned strike action, under the mediation of
the Labor Department of the local government.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting convened by the Labor Department, representatives
from the China Motor Bus (CMB) management and the Motor Transport
Workers General Union "reached the agreement over the terms of
settlement for the dismissal of 45 mechanics."
</P>
<P>
