<HEADLINE> EU Supports Projects for Integration of Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 13 (Xinhua) -- A European Union (EU)
official today announced that the European Commission, the EU's
executive agency, would support a total of 59 projects aimed at
assisting the integration of refugees in member states.
</P>
<P>
Padraig Flynn, EU commissioner responsible for employment and
social affairs, said the projects concern education and training,
labor market integration, housing, guidance and counseling, access
to services, social protection, culture and leisure activities.
</P>
<P>
"I consider it an important step forward that the Commission
has been able to support -- for the first time -- the social and
economic integration of refugees in member states," said Flynn.
</P>
<P>
He said that "a very large number of interesting projects" had
been submitted despite a tight implementation schedule and high
eligibility standards.
</P>
<P>
"I am impressed with the overall quality and scope of the
projects submitted and, in particular, those we have been able to
select for funding," the commissioner said.
</P>
<P>
The selected projects were reportedly submitted by private or
public bodies and organizations at local, regional, national and
European levels. Some funding has been made available for projects
at the European level. 
</P>
