<HEADLINE> China Calls for Drug Education for Its Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The China National Narcotics
Control Commission and the State Education Commission recently
issued a circular, calling for education about
drugs among students in primary and middle schools and
institutions of higher learning.
</P>
<P>
The circular pointed out that the anti-drug move is a serious
matter related to social stability and the future of the country,
and that halting the emergence of new drug addicts is a major task
listed in the country's Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
To provide education about drugs among students and to keep them
away from drugs is an extremely important work that will help prevent
the spread of drugs, it says.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
