<HEADLINE> Australia, Eqypt Advance into World Team Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Australia and Egypt
advanced into the semi-finals of the Men's World Squash Team
Championship with 3-0 wins over South Africa and Pakistan
respectively.
</P>
<P>
They were joined in the semis by Canada and England, who also
cruised to 3-0 victories over their opponents, Malaysia and
Finland.
</P>
<P>
Newly-crowned singles champion Rodney Eyles was stretched for
43 minutes before edging South African Craig Wapnick 9-6, 9-6, 9-4.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Brett Martin, known as one of the best stroke
players on the circuit, then beat Glen Whittaker 9-4, 9-5, 9-4.
</P>
<P>
In the dead-rubber, Dan Jenson defeated Craig Van der Wath 5-9,
9-0, 9-2 to help Australia clinch the winning point.
</P>
<P>
Ahmad Barada gave his team Egypt the lead by defeating
Pakistan's Zubair Jahan Khan 9-0, 4-9, 9-3 and 9-1.
</P>
<P>
Omar El Borolossy crushed Amjad Khan 9-3, 9-1 and 9-6 in the
second round.
</P>
<P>
Amir Wagih completed the rout for Egypt by finishing off Kumail
Mehmoo 9-7, 9-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
