<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Beats Michael Chang in ATP Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia
scored his second victory at the ATP World Championships, beating
Michael Chang of the United States 6-3, 6-0 in Hanover, Germany on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian, who needed to lift the trophy at his home Kremlin
Cup on Sunday in order to get a place in the eight-man field,
added the world No. 2 to a White group victim's list this week
which includes Swede Jonas Bjorkman.
</P>
<P>
Chang, who is fighting to hold down his elite ranking place
behind Pete Sampras as U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter of
Australia presses for the No. 2 spot, stands 1-1 with a final
match to play.
</P>
<P>
The top two players in two groups qualify for Saturday's
semifinals at the end-of-season affair.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman and Spain's Sergi Bruguera were playing later
Thursday. 
</P>
