<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Inder
Kumar Gujral has called for more attention to women's education,
saying that it would be the key to the progress and development of
countries like India, local press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating a three-day world conference on education in India
on Wednesday, Gujral emphasized the need for changing the mindset
of the society on women's education.
</P>
<P>
