inhibit the progress of women. There are social mindsets which
come in the way of women's education," he said.
</P>
<P>
He called for more attention to women's education, especially
primary education and literacy.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need for launching a people's movement to
tackle the problem of illiteracy which he said was one of the
major obstacles to India's progress and development. 
