<HEADLINE> China Basketball League to Begin in Late November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese basketball giant the
August First Rockets will begin to defend their title of the
Chinese Professional Basketball League on November 23.
</P>
<P>
According to a press conference here on Thursday, the August
First will meet strong challenge from other 11 clubs which include
96/97 season's runners-up the Liaoning Hunters and third place
finishers Guangdong Hongyuan.
</P>
<P>
In the preliminary round last season, the August First lost to
Liaoning Hunters 80-92 and Guangdong Hongyuan 90-100.
</P>
<P>
The other nine teams are Shandong Baoyuan, Jiangsu Nangang,
Shanghai Oriental, Lianhang Eagles, Shenyang Army, Beijing
Shougang, Sichuan Panda, Zhejiang Zhongxin and Jinan Army Pegasus.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhizhi, who led the August First for the crown last
season, did not expect any easy competitions for the title holders.
</P>
<P>
"We will face a more competitive season. What we should do is
to try our best to win every single game," he said at the press
conference.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Wang Zhizhi, who had the most blocks last
season, will be joined by Adijiang, Li Nan, Zhang Jinsong and Liu
Yudong, all of whom are among the national lines-up, in the August
First team.
</P>
<P>
The army club, which had a clean sweep of national champions in
the past, made a 19-3 running in the preliminary round and scored
a 100-percent winning record in play-offs on its way to winning
the title last season.
</P>
<P>
In order to increase the popularity of the sports in China, new
system will be adopted in the play off round during the new season.
</P>
<P>
After the preliminary round, the best eight teams will play in
the cross-elimination series home and away for new placings. All
play-off games will be played on the basis of best of three with
the championship game best of five.
</P>
<P>
The new season will end on April 1, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
