<HEADLINE> China's Stance on Iraq Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- China is fully prepared to
maintain consultations and cooperation with all parties concerned
to settle the crisis with Iraq at the earliest possible date,
according to Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang.
</P>
<P>
Shen made the remarks today at a press conference in response
to a question concerning China's stance on the Iraqi issue and the
unanimous resolution passed by the UN Security Council.
</P>
<P>
China is "highly concerned about the developments of the Iraq
Issue" and "appreciates the efforts the parties concerned have
made to solve the issue," Shen said.
</P>
<P>
China maintains that the Security Council resolutions on
the Iraq issue should be implemented in a comprehensive and
practical manner, and that Iraq should immediately carry out its
obligations by restoring full cooperation with the United Nations,
said Shen.
</P>
<P>
China's UN ambassador, president of the Security Council since
the beginning of the crisis, has consistently called for calm and
restraint from all the parties concerned, and has firmly proposed to
resolve issues through dialogue and cooperation in order to
avoid escalation of the situation, especially armed conflict,
said Shen, adding that "we have consistently engaged in
constructive efforts to reach this end."
</P>
<P>
