<HEADLINE> Spaniards Held for Smuggling of Gun Parts in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Three Spanish nationals were
held Wednesday night at an international airport here for trying
to bring in a suitcase filled with gun parts, the Philippine News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
At the Ninoy Aquino International Airport, customs police
detected the gun parts stuffed in a large suitcase checked in by
the three Spanish passengers.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines' law prohibits anyone from importing guns or
gun parts without permit from the country's Firearms and
Explosives Office.
</P>
<P>
The three Spanish nationals are being investigated to find out
who their connections or consignees are in Manila.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said the three could be charged with illegal
possession of firearms even if what have been confiscated from
them are gun parts and accessories.
</P>
<P>
Among the gun parts brought in by the three suspects include a
number of barrels, recoil springs and stabilizers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
