<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Nomination of candidates for
the 36 deputies of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) of China
began today.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 people obtained Registration Forms for Applicants
for the Election of Deputies of the HKSAR to the Ninth NPC today.
</P>
<P>
The registration forms filled in by the applicants must be
handed in before 18:00 hours on November 28, the deadline set for
nomination, together with nomination letters signed by at least 10
members of the 424-strong Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
Two applicants had waited outside the registration office
before it was opened at 9 o'clock this morning. Witnessed by more
than 50 reporters, Lai King Tim got the first application form.
</P>
<P>
Lai told reporters that it is important to take part in the
election because this is his sacred right as a Chinese citizen
living in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Kennedy Wong Ying-ho, member of the Provisional Legislative
Council of the HKSAR, came to get his registration form this
morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that since Hong Kong has returned to China, Hong Kong
people should take an active part in the management of state
affairs.
</P>
<P>
This election is very important as it is the first time for
Hong Kong to elect its own deputies to the NPC as an independent
constituency, he added.
</P>
<P>
Professor Lau Pui-king of the Hong Kong Polytechnic University
said that she often travels to the inland areas not as a tourist
but as a scholar to study the economic reform in the inland.
</P>
<P>
She has been elected twice to the NPC as a member of the
delegation of Guangdong province and this is her first time to
apply for NPC candidate in Hong Kong.
</P>
