<HEADLINE> Two Foreigners Deported from Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government has
deported a South African and a Briton for their alleged racist
behaviour, Principal Immigration Officer Frank Kwinga has said.
</P>
<P>
The principal immigration officer said on Wednesday
that Alan Reynolds, a South African, left the country on Tuesday,
and British Wesley Winter, left abroad a London bound British
Airways flight on Monday, accordling to a Daily Nation report
today.
</P>
<P>
He said: "We cannot allow people to bring Nyoko Nyoko
(trouble) here. We are independent and we should be respected."
</P>
<P>
Last Saturday, Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi cautioned that
the government would not tolerate arrogant and insolent foreign
employees who abused Africans.
</P>
<P>
He demanded the South African, Alan Reynolds, to stop
insulting black employees, or "pack up and go home". He asked
the Briton to stop similar behaviour.
</P>
<P>
The people of Kenya are not ready to sell their dignity and
self-esteem for foreign investment, Moi stressed.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the South African, who came to Kenya in
1976 as an employee of Twiga Chemicals, was boasting that he came
from a more civilized community.
</P>
<P>
Wesley Winter was picked up at his company's office in the
industrial area in Nairobi and taken to Jomo Kenyatta
International Airport, according to Kenya's Immigration
Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
