<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao to Address Computer Millennium Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Macao government has taken
measures to address the millennium problem on computers and it
hopes all computers at government departments will be immune from
the problem by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Administrative and Civil Service Department
(ACSD) recently conducted a survey among 25 computerized
departments of the government. Half of the 16 respondents say that
they have started re-programming the computers to avoid the
so-called "millennium bug", while the others are making assessment
and plans for the move.
</P>
<P>
Due to problems in programming, the "bug" will lead computers
to make wrong judgment when it comes to the year 2000. If not
adjusted, experts say, it will cause damages, sometimes very
serious.  
</P>
</TEXT>
