<HEADLINE> Chinese, Yugoslav Army Chiefs Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA) has adopted a positive attitude toward
promoting friendship and cooperation with the Yugoslav armed
forces based on mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Chinese General Fu Quanyou, chief of the PLA General Staff,
made the remarks today during a meeting with his Yugoslav
counterpart Momcilo Perisic, who is accompanying Yugoslav
President Slobodan Milosevic on a state visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Fu noted that China and Yugoslavia have enjoyed a long history
of cooperation, and that their peoples share deep feelings of
friendship.
</P>
<P>
He said, Chinese President Jiang Zemin announced in his report
to the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
that China will reduce its armed forces by half a million
people over the next three years. The new round of reduction
will follow a one-million-man reduction in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The move shows that China is a major power to maintain world
peace, and that the PLA is devoted to safeguarding peace, said Fu.
</P>
<P>
Perisic briefed Fu on the European situation and Yugoslavia's
domestic affairs. He expressed the hope that relations between the two
armed forces will continue to grow. 
</P>
