<HEADLINE> Ukraine Footballer Banned for Two Years for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine banned midfielder Serhiy
Nahornyak from competition for two years on Thursday for failing a
drugs test.
</P>
<P>
The chief doctor of Nayornyak's club side, Dnipro
Dnipropetrovsk, was banned for life from the Ukrainian league.
</P>
<P>
Nahornyak failed a routine test for Bromantan after Ukraine
lost 2-0 to Croatia in their first leg of the World Cup play-off
in Zagreb on October 29.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Ukrainian Football Federation said the
26-year-old was banned from all national and international
competition until December 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
It was the first positive test out of 19 random samples
conducted by FIFA during the qualifying series and the first in
the World Cup since Diego Maradona tested positive during the
finals in the United States three years ago. 
</P>
