<HEADLINE> Nanning-Kunming Railway in SW China to Be Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The 898.7-km Nanning-Kunming
Railway, a major project in southwest China, will open to traffic
on December 1.
</P>
<P>
The railway linking the capitals of the Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region and Yunan
province is expected to spark economic growth in the southwestern
region, a new focus of national economic development.
</P>
<P>
Bridges and tunnels account for 31 percent of the total length
of the railway. The 10-km Mihualing Tunnel is the longest
single-track railway tunnel in China.
</P>
<P>
The railway's annual hauling capacity will be five million
tons for the first-stage project and 10 million tons for the second
phase. 
</P>
