<HEADLINE> Shanghai Institute of Biochemistry Marks 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 13 (Xinhua) -- China's only biochemistry
research center celebrated its 40th anniversary Wednesday in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Institute of Biochemistry under the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS) lead all of its international counterparts in
making synthetic crystalline bovine insulin and synthetic yeast
alanine.
</P>
<P>
The well-known research center on molecular biology and genetic
engineering also published 24 academic books and more than 4,000
research papers. In the years from 1990 to 1996 it scored 20
prominent international achievements in this field.
</P>
<P>
In addition, many young scientists have been fostered there,
said officials from the institute. 
