<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Works out Plan to Solve Environmental Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
worked out a national environment management action plan in an
effort to solve the country's environmental problems, the national
news agency BSS reported today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a three-day meeting of the South Asia Association
of Regional Cooperation (SAARC) Technical Committee on Environment
and Meteorology here Wednesday, Environment and Forest Minister
Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury said that "the process of preparing the
national environment management action plan is highly
participatory involving NGOs, academicians, parliamentarians,
lawyers, journalists and people at the grassroot levels."
</P>
<P>
A national environmental committee has been formed under the
chairmanship of the prime minister in this regard, she said.
</P>
<P>
She said that "We are now able to reduce the extent of damage
caused by natural disasters with the improved forecasting
early-warning services, adequate prior preparedness, timely
management and massive afforestation program in the coastal
areas."
</P>
<P>
The enormous loss of human lives and properties caused by
natural disasters and degradation of environment, she pointed out,
are two of the most serious problems of this South Asian country,
which are mostly meteorological phenomena that hinder the economic
development and growth.
</P>
<P>
She noted that Bangladesh is a constant victim of natural
disasters such as cyclones, tidal surges, floods, tornadoes,
torrential rain and droughts which always cause havoc every year
to human lives and property.
</P>
<P>
The rapid degradation of environment in the region is a serious
concern to the people and the governments of the SAARC countries,
she noted.
</P>
<P>
She said regional cooperation among the SAARC nations is a must
to provide a basis for the member countries to draw up policy
measures and recommendations keeping in view the potential and
possibilities of evolving a regional plan of action.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
