<HEADLINE> Jiu San Society Closes 7th National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh National Congress
of Jiu San (September 9th) Society closed today with Wu Jieping
re-elected as Chairman of the Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jieping, a noted medical scientist and educator, currently
serves as vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
People's Congress and is an academician with the Chinese Academy
of Sciences and Academy of Engineering.
</P>
<P>
The congress approved the "Report of the Ninth Central
Committee of the Jiu San Society" and the amended "Program of the
Jiu San Society". It also elected 225 members to serve on the 10th
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Jiu San Society is mainly composed of senior and mid-level
intellectuals from the fields of science, technology, culture,
education, medical and health care.
</P>
<P>
The society was founded in 1944 as the "Democracy and Science
Society" and was renamed the "Jiu San Society" on May 4, 1946, in
commemoration of the victory in the Anti-Japanese War which fell
on September 3, 1945.  
</P>
</TEXT>
