<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Higher on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices fell during the
day's trading but only finished higher on the Singapore market as
the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index gained 4.9 points to
end at 1,690.69 points today.
</P>
<P>
The day's slide came in the wake of a sharp 157-point sell-off
on Wall Street overnight. However dealers here said that there was
no urgency to sell. They noted that buyers were on the sidelines
and the volume had gone dead.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was almost steady at 142.38 million
units, worth 282.59 million Singapore dollars (about 179.99
million US dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 217 to 103,
while 292 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 11.35 million units. It was followed by
JIT which had 11.1 million shares traded. RHB Capital Warrant99
was next with 6.95 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 70 cents to end at 44.8 Singapore dollars.
DelGro 500 increased by 45 cents to close at seven Singapore
dollars, while the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) picked up by 40
cents to finish at 15.2 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Uniphoenix was the biggest loser as it
declined by 55 cents to close at 5.55 Singapore dollars. The
United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign fell by 40 cents to finish at
9.1 Singapore dollars and local property developer City
Developments lost 35 cents to end at 7.05 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
