<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Market for Interior Decoration Booming in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Civilian household interior
decorations have become popular consumer items here, with the
local market climbing to 20 billion yuan a year.
</P>
<P>
More than 200,000 households move into new homes or improve
living conditions each year in Shanghai, according to local
sources. As living standards improve, more and more local
residents are motivated to decorate their homes to drive up demand.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of construction in Shanghai said that in
past years the average family spent about 50,000 yuan to decorate
an apartment, and a family with better income often spent double
that or more on decorations.
</P>
<P>
Taking 50,000 yuan as an average household expenditure for
interior decoration, the yearly market demand would total 12
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In addition, redecorating the city's old apartments also will
increase decorative market demands, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The ever-growing market for decorations has advanced the
development of businesses dealing in sanitary utensils, electrical
appliances, building materials and construction.
</P>
<P>
About 300 professional companies specialize in interior
decoration in the city, according to the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
