<HEADLINE> Chemical Cloud Scares Away Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, November 12 (Xinhua) -- More than 600 local
residents in Paso Robles County, 160 miles northwest of Los
Angeles, fled homes, offices and workshops this morning when
a chemical pipeline broke, sending the gray chemical cloud
into the sky, according to a report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place about 4:00 a.m. at a chemical plant in
Paso Robles County.
</P>
<P>
The leak was stopped and the toxic cloud disappeared at 9:00
a.m.
</P>
<P>
The National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health said
the toxic smoke can cause choking, nausea and abdominal pain.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the pipeline break is under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
