<HEADLINE> 296 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 296.85 kilograms of
Heroin were captured by a Myanmar patrolling column of defense
services at Kaung Kway village near the Myanmar-China border on
Tuesday morning, the Myanmar authorities confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
When the Myanmar patrolling column searched a house at the
village, 818 blocks and 40 plastic bags of heroin totaling 296.85
kilograms were found, and another 61.2 kilograms of opium, two
M-22 guns, nine grenades and two vehicles were also captured.
</P>
<P>
The authorities also seized 10 suspects along with the drugs
and paraphernalia.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the Myanmar authorities have
destroyed 25 heroin refineries in Shan state of the country since
the beginning of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
