<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Accelerates Construction of Basic Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The north China province
of Hebei has allocated 371.2 billion yuan for the construction of
basic industries and infrastructure facilities since the end of
1992, with related funding growing by an average 40.3 percent
annually.
</P>
<P>
The province's power generation network has a combined capacity
of more than ten million kw, and a number of key water control
projects have either been completed or are under construction,
including the Taolinkow Reservoir, and a project to divert water
from the Yellow River to Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Other projects include the 370-km Hebei section of the
Beijing-Kowloon Railway, expressing stretching 315 km, the
Shijiazhuang Airport, and a number of ports and berths.
</P>
<P>
The province's posts and telecommunications volume hit 4.9
billion yuan last year, up 5.7-fold on the 1991 level.
</P>
<P>
Local officials note that related facilities will promote
economic growth in Hebei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
