<HEADLINE> Kenya Imposes Visa Rule on Britons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government has
decided to impose visa requirements beginning on November 15 on
all British passport holders entering the country, said Kenyan
immigration department officials.
</P>
<P>
The daily newspaper Times today quoted Immigration
officials as saying that it was in response
to Britain's decision on visas requirements for Kenyans.
</P>
<P>
The British government imposed visa rules on Kenyans on March
7, last year.
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the British High Commission to Kenya said
Wednesday that the High Commission was informed of Kenya's
decision on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's Principal Immigration officer Frank Kwinga said,
"It is only fair and diplomatically acceptable
that Britons entering Kenya have visas just like Kenyans entering
Britain are required to have visas."
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Foreign Minister Kalonzo Musyoka said that it was not
in the East African country's interest to reciprocate.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that about 100,000 British tourists visit
Kenya each year and Kenya's decision will add the cost of
holidays in Kenya for British citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
