<HEADLINE> Rare Bird Species on South China Sea Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, November 13 (Xinhua) -- A flock of several hundred rare
yellow-beaked white heron, a species under state protection, live
on Dongdao Island which is part of the Xisha Islands in the South
China Sea.
</P>
<P>
The rare species, which is seldom seen on China's mainland, has
readily adapted to the presence of local residents. Flocks of
heron most often perch in palm trees.
</P>
<P>
Dongdao island, located some 200 nautical miles southeast of
Hainan, China's southernmost island province, is also home to
several thousand boobies, another rare bird species under state
protection. 
