<HEADLINE> Nanjing Holds Painting Exhibition On Sun Yat-sen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- A major painting and
calligraphy exhibition themed "Dr. Sun Yat-sen and Overseas
Chinese" has opened in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
Jointly sponsored by a Hong Kong-based cultural foundation and
related Chinese departments, the exhibition marks the 131st
anniversary of the birth of Dr. Sun Yat-sen, who led China's
democratic revolution and overthrew the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911).
</P>
<P>
On display are over 100 paintings and calligraphy works by more
than 100 artists from both sides of the Taiwan Straits, Australia,
Singapore, Malaysia, France, the Philippines, and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Sun Yat-sen's spirit to save the nation and the people are
fully reflected in the work.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony yesterday, Yew Sim Liong,
chairman of Nanyuan Yin Fong Group Company, said that as the
sponsor, he hoped that overseas Chinese will carry forward the
honored tradition of Dr. Sun and contribute to the modernization
drive of their motherland.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is also expected to travel to other big cities
in China as well as Singapore, Japan, Europe and North
America. 
</P>
