<HEADLINE> Air Zimbabwe Incurs Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Air Zimbabwe Corporation
(AIRZIM) incurred an operational loss of more than 150 million
Zimbabwe Dollars (12 million U.S. dollars) this year, AIRZIM'S
Chief Executive Officer Brendon Donohoe announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Bulawayo Publicity Association annual meeting,
Donohoe said strikes and bad management had contributed to the
financial loss.
</P>
<P>
"A majority of our problems were that management lost focus,
staff lost confidence, and the airline was run on a personality
basis," he said.
</P>
<P>
The corporation had introduced new flight schedules designed
to utilise equipment in a bid to be competitive.
</P>
<P>
On the commercialisation, Donohoe said the process was well on
track and expected to be complete by April next year.
</P>
<P>
"We also have to carry out studies, exercises and evaluations
to see what route network we should operate, and what equipment
is required to serve it," Donohoe said. 
</P>
