<HEADLINE> Rice Production Totals 5.45 Million Tons in SKorea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, November 13 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's rice production
for this year is estimated at 5.45 million tons, the largest since
1990, according to the report from the Agriculture and Forest
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
South Korea produced 5.607 million tons of rice in 1990.
</P>
<P>
In a final tally, the ministry said that this year's production
is 2.4 percent more than last year and 1.8 percent more than the
estimation made on September 15.
</P>
<P>
A ministry official said that the high yield is attributed to
good weather, prevention of harmful insects and diseases, and an
overall increase of farmland.
</P>
<P>
The unit production, which is 505 kilograms per acre in Japan,
averages 518 kilograms per acre in South Korea, the largest in the
country's rice farming history, and more than the record of 507
kilograms posted last year, he added.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, Australia produced 635 kilograms of grain per
acre, Egypt 598 kilograms and Greece 583 kilograms, respectively,
in 1996, according to the ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
