backdrop of increased competition. It shows we are still the
market leaders, a position we are confident we will retain,'' the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
COTTCO is one of the first state enterprises to be privatised
and still controls 70 percent of the country's cotton market with
the rest shared among its three competitors.
</P>
<P>
The company recently had a share offer which saw 75 percent of
the company's shares purchased leaving the government with only
25 percent shareholding.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said it was their goal to have the company
listed on the Zimbabwe Stock Exchange by early December. 
