<HEADLINE> Province Sets Record for Cotton Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- China's central agricultural
province of Hunan has gathered in a record harvest of cotton this
year with more than 120,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Hybrid cotton technology was credited with the record harvest
by officials with the provincial agricultural department. More
than 106,000 hectares of hybrid cotton were planted, accounting
for half of the province's cotton-growing areas.
</P>
<P>
The per-unit area yield of the hybrid cotton is above 1,500
kilograms, a 12 percent increase over the normal breed.
</P>
<P>
The hybrid cotton raised in the province has been improved
after 20-plus years of efforts by local scientists. The State
Science and Technology Commission has set up a hybrid cotton
breeding center in the province. In addition, the Ministry of
Agriculture has designated the hybrid as a key breed for
nationwide use.
</P>
<P>
The province has promulgated a series of policies to help
farmers grow the high-yield cotton and to guarantee their
enthusiasm in planting it.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that the province's hybrid planting area will reach
150,000 hectares next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
