<HEADLINE> Subway in Guangzhou Becomes a Popular Tourist Attraction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Over 300,000 people have
taken the new subway in Guangzhou since it opened to traffic four
months ago -- but for sightseeing rather than commuting.
</P>
<P>
As the first section of the subway is still in trial operation,
the five-stop trip takes a full hour to cover. Though the fare for
the short trip is five yuan, which is expensive by Chinese
standards, it is still attractive to tourists who like the
distinctly different feel of traveling underground.
</P>
<P>
To satisfy the travelers' curiosity, the Guangzhou Subway
Company has designated the trial operation as the "sightseeing
period," providing a ten-minute stop at each station for visitors
to take pictures and a non-stop return trip. 
