<HEADLINE> Southwest China Develops Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Six provinces in southwest
China plan to expand cooperation to develop tourism.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan, Guizhou, Yunnan, Guangxi, the Tibet Autonomous Region,
and Chongqing will develop 12 tour itineraries stressing
"ecology-friendly" tourism.
</P>
<P>
The regions have also agreed to jointly host a major tourism
fair every two years beginning in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China, one of China's most popular tourism areas,
offers numerous attractions, including the charming landscape of
Guilin in Guangxi, the unique folklore of Xishuangbanna in Yunnan
Province, the magnificent Three Gorges on the Yangtze River,
scenic Ermei Mountain and the mysterious Jiuzhaigou Scenic Area in
Sichuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
