<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ICRC Helps Ugandan War Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 13 (Xinhua) --The International Committee of
the Red Cross (ICRC ) has donated food, blankets, and medicines
to victims of war and internal violence in western and nothern
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Local daily "The Monitor" today quoted a recent ICRC report as
reporting that medicines and other medical supplies donated to
Ugandan clinics and hospitals in western districts of Kabarole
and Kasese cost 15,000 U.S.Dollars.
</P>
<P>
In northern district of Koboko, 22,000 people will benefit
from a water rehabilitation program funded by ICRC and the
Ugandan Red Cross Society, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile,ICRC had provided food to 26,500 people in koboko
and Maracha counties in northern Uganda, the report said.
</P>
<P>
A dispensary in Koboko which had stopped functioning due to
insecurity resumed operation in July owing to the donation of
essential medicines and other medical supplies from the ICRC.
</P>
</TEXT>
