<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Rupee Dips to 21-month Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Indian rupee fell to a
21-month low to touch 36.76 rupees against the U.S. dollar at the
inter-bank foreign exchange market in Bombay, India, on Wednesday,
the local press said today.
</P>
<P>
Even though the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) intervened heavily
in the spot and forward segments of the market by selling an
estimated 400 million dollars, the rupee continued to show
excessive volatility.
</P>
<P>
Opening at 36.67/69 rupees per dollar, the rupee went for a
roller-coaster ride.
</P>
<P>
The RBI, the central bank, intervened when the rupee touched
36.72, and brought it down to the 36.70 rupee level. But
persistent demand for dollars saw the rupee hitting a new low of
36.76.  
</P>
</TEXT>
