<HEADLINE> Chinese Soccer Squad Promise to Do Better in Open Letter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, Northeastern China, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese
soccer squad, which failed to reach the French World Cup Finals
early this month, on Thursday promised in an open letter to
Chinese fans that they will "wipe off tears and try to catch up
with Asian soccer powerhouses".
</P>
<P>
"We let you down again," said the open letter. "We are
overwhelmed by remorse and self-scolding... We want to say a
sincere 'sorry' to everyone."
</P>
<P>
The letter said that, from China's fifth failed World Cup try,
the team found out that "they knew little about the
rapidly-developing world of soccer and the Chinese team needed
improvements on management, training and quality of the players."
</P>
<P>
"We would thoroughly review our qualifying competition and sum
up the lessons," the letter added.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, some disappointed Chinese fans at Jinzhou Stadium
here booed the home team and cheered for the visiting Kuwaiti
eleven in a meaningless group match.
</P>
<P>
China, which has never made the World Cup Finals, won 1-0 to
finish third after Saudi Arabia and Iran in group A of the Asian
Zone qualifying competition, whose winner automatically goes to
France and runner-up has to vie for a remaining Asian berth with
Japan.  
</P>
