<HEADLINE> Gansu Promotes Compulsory Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu
Province will extend great effort to fully develop the Nine-Year
Compulsory Education Program in 50 poverty-stricken counties by
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
"The central and provincial governments will invest a total of
640 million yuan (80 million US dollars) in the program which
covers primary and middle schools in 39 state-level and 11
provincial-level poor counties", according to a local education
official.
</P>
<P>
The funds will help the counties improve elementary education,
establish training programs for primary and middle school
teachers, build new schools and refurbish buildings, as well as
purchase textbooks, chairs and desks, and provide teaching
equipment and materials.
</P>
<P>
"The province has introduced the program to 29 poor counties in
recent years, with 97 percent of school-age children in related
areas receiving an elementary education." according to the
official. 
