<HEADLINE>   Third Sea Port to be Set Up in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government is
actively considering to set up the third sea port in the country,
the national news agency BSS reported here today.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed on Wednesday by Finance Minister Shah AMS
Kibria while addressing a seminar titled "Pre-Shipment Inspection
(PSI)" held in Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
"We are considering providing a deep sea port in the country
and further development of Chittagong Port and Mongla Port," the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the government is committed to ensure a free and
steady flow of trade in this South Asian country to boost the
economy rapidly, the minister said that at present the government
is interested in smooth export-import business and proper revenue
collection.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the PSI system, the minister said, "PSI was a
voluntary system, the introduction of the system was a mistake in
Bangladesh context. It was a faulty system, which ultimately
caused a serious loss of government revenue in the past."
</P>
<P>
The minister stated that the government will continue its
present economic policy but would consider all economic suggestion
which would bring good for the country and not only for any group.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
