<HEADLINE> Export of Coffee up in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's coffee exports
totaled 2.31 billion U.S. dollars in the first 10 months of 1997,
an 80.1 percent-increase over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Federation of Coffee Exporters (Febec) said today that
in the period, the exports amounted to 12.2 million sacks, 28.4
percent up from January-October 1996.
</P>
<P>
Brazil plans to sell 16.6 million sacks abroad to earn 3.1
billion dollars this year, Febec said.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, the world's biggest coffee producer and exporter, sold
13 million sacks out of a total of 26 million and pocketed 1.688
billion dollars in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
