<HEADLINE> Thai Premier Chuan Leekpai to be Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan
Leekpai has decided to name himself defense minister, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The final cabinet list of 48 ministers holding 50 seats is now
being vetted by Cabinet Secretary-General Visanu Kreua-Ngam to
determine if any of the cabinet members fails to meet the
qualification laid down in the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
The list is scheduled to submit to King Bhumibul Adulyadej
Friday, then a royal command will officially install the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Chuan Leekpai was appointed as new prime minister by a royal
command on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chuan's decision to assume the defense portfolio will make him
the first civilian to hold the post in the Thai history.
</P>
<P>
A source of the Democrat Party led by Chuan Leekpai was quoted
as saying that Chuan's move stemmed from the fears that some
elements with military connections might use the military to
destabilize the government.  
</P>
