<HEADLINE> Maldives Seeks Sri Lankan Assistance to Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 13 (Xinhua) -- The Maldives has sought
assistance from the Sri Lankan Higher Education Ministry and
universities to establish a higher education academy in the
country, informed sources disclosed here today.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Education Minister Richard Pathirana and Maldivian
High Commissioner Abdul Aziz recently discussed the feasibility of
setting up such an institute, the sources from the Higher
Education Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Under the assistance program, Sri Lankan education expertise
will help design and initiate the higher education institution in
the Maldives. Sri Lankan lecturers will also teach at the
institution after its establishment.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the academy is expected to be set up next
year while Aziz said that the Maldives expects all assistance from
the Sri Lankan Government to fulfill the project.
</P>
<P>
By now the two sides have not decided how much they will spend
on this proposed academy, the sources added. 
