<HEADLINE> Czech Police Crack First Pedophilic Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Czech police successfully
cracked an international pedophilic ring in a predawn operation
Tuesday, detaining five suspects, an interior ministry spokesman
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jan Subert said the case was the first of its kind ever cracked
in the Czech Republic, and that the five suspects were three
French, one American and one Briton.
</P>
<P>
For long, this criminal ring had collaborated with
international pedophilic gangs in sexually abusing a number of
children aged between six and 18, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In doing so, they had forced sex on the victims and filmed or
video-taped the scenes before selling their works overseas to seek
huges illegal gains, according to him.
</P>
<P>
These criminals also forced the victims to take drugs.
</P>
<P>
Subert said foreign pedophilic organizations were running
rampant in the Czech Republic and that the government will
continue to crack down on such organized crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
