<HEADLINE> One Billion Yuan Spent On Hydro-electric Power Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1.49 billion yuan
has been spent on construction work on the Dachaoshan
Hydro-electric power station on the Lancang River in southwest
China.
</P>
<P>
A water diversion tunnel, a key part of the construction, went
into service in May of last year.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen hydro-electric power stations with a combined capacity
of 22 million kw are planned for the Lancang, which is on the
upper reaches of the Mekong River.
</P>
<P>
Dachaoshan is the second hydro-electric power plant on the
Lanchang. It will have an installed capacity of 1.35 million kw
and will be able to generate 5.9 billion kw/hour of electricity in
a year.
</P>
<P>
The Dachaoshan Hydropower Development Co. Ltd., which was
established by the State Development Investment Company, the
Hongta Industrial Co. Ltd. of Yunnan Province, the Yunnan
Provincial Development and Investment Corporation, and the Yunnan
Provincial Power Company are in charge of financing and
construction.
</P>
<P>
The entire project is expected to cost 8.87 billion yuan. The
four companies have put up 1.77 billion yuan in capital. Recently,
the State Development Bank decided to provide Dachaoshan station
with 4.2 billion yuan in loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
