<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Maintain Austerity Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia will stay with its
policy of monetary austerity, the Central Bank governor,
J. Unenbat, said here today.
</P>
<P>
It will try to keep fluctuation of the exchange rate between
its tugrik and the U.S. dollar under five percent to curb
inflation, maintain macro-economic stability and provide better
circumstances for more foreign investment, production and
operation, Unenbat said.
</P>
<P>
The monetary austerity policy taken this year had proved
effective, he said, and the inflation rate in the first 10 months
of the year was 14.3 percent, significantly lower than last year,
</P>
<P>
Mongolia has a net foreign exchange reserve of 800 million
U.S. dollars now, 300 million more than at the beginning of this
year, and the economy at large is stable, the governor added.
</P>
