<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Beijing Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Beijing
is increasing with more foreign firms running businesses in
China's capital.
</P>
<P>
From January to September this year Beijing approved 578 new
foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The total contracted investment from the newly approved foreign
businesses increased about 45 percent to 1.46 billion U.S. dollars
in the first nine months of this year over the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Of the investment, 59.2 percent went to the service trade, an
increase of 15 percentage points over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
There are 50 newly approved, foreign-funded projects whose
total investment sum exceeds 10 million U.S. dollars each.
</P>
<P>
Four foreign banks have opened branches in Beijing this year
and the number of total banks in the capital city now is 13.
</P>
<P>
So far, 140 of the 500 largest transnational corporations in
the world have invested in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
