<HEADLINE> China, U.S. Jointly Develop New Minibus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Trial production of a new
minibus in Jiangxi Province has been termed a success, with the
assembly line expected to start rolling early next month.
</P>
<P>
The annual production capacity for the "Transit," jointly
developed by the Jiangling Automobile Industry Corp. and the
American car giant Ford Motor Co., is expected to reach 20,000,
according to Sun Min, chairman of the Jiangling company.
</P>
<P>
"The vehicles will not only be sold in China but also overseas
through the sales network of Ford," Sun said.
</P>
<P>
While the Transit has been a favorite in Europe for some time,
experts say the new model turned out by Jiangling is believed to
be even better than its European counterpart.
</P>
<P>
A leading carmaker in China, Jiangling has an annual assembly
capacity of 60,000.
</P>
<P>
Ford's cooperation with Jiangling started in 1995 when the
U.S. firm bought a 30 percent stake in Jiangling.
</P>
<P>
China's annual demand for commercial cars is estimated at
200,000 and the prospect for the new Transit will be good,
predicted experts at the State Information Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
