<HEADLINE> Olympiakos Suffers First Euroleague Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian champion CSKA Moscow
reapt its home victory over Olympiakos, forcing the latter to
suffer its first Euroleague defeat of the season here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian cagers stunned the visiting Greek nationals 77-58.
</P>
<P>
After a tough first half, the Russians enjoyed a 12-3 run
midway through the second half, thanks to the accurate three-point
shooting of Valery Daineko, the game's top scorer with 19 points.
</P>
<P>
CSKA, showing great discipline in defence, was able to control
Olympiakos's powerful attack, and Lithuanian Arturas Karnisovas,
last season's European player of the year, was cornered to only 11
points.
</P>
<P>
Despite the defeat, the Euroleague champions still led group A
with six wins from seven matches. CSKA are second after four wins
and three defeats. 
</P>
