<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Qualifies for World Cup Finals With Last Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia defeated Qatar 1-0
Wednesday in the last match of the World Cup Asian qualifying zone
Group A to claim a berth for the World Cup finals slated next year
in France.
</P>
<P>
The Saudis, who won Asia's second automatic ticket along with
Group B winner South Korea, topped the group with 14 points,
followed by Iran with 12.
</P>
<P>
Winners of the playoff between Iran and Japan, runners-up in
the two groups, will book the third berth in the Asian Zone, while
the loser will take on Australia for the other spot in the World
Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Sami Al Jaber scored the winner in the 63rd minute when he
flung down the right side to drive the ball into the right corner
of the net.
</P>
<P>
As Saudi goalie Mohammad al-Daeyia made great efforts to defend
his territory, his teammates eventually blocked Qatar's attacks to
hold their advantage for good. 
</P>
