<HEADLINE> Chinese Tourists Satisfied With Shanghai's Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 13 (Xinhua) -- Tourism authorities in
Shanghai have done a lot to improve the city's tourism sector in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
A recent on-the-spot survey by the Municipal Social-Economic
Investigation Team showed that the effort has paid off, with 80
percent of the tourists coming from other parts of China
questioned expressing satisfaction with the city's services and
facilities.
</P>
<P>
The 16,500 people questioned, who came from other parts of the
country, said that famous bands are a popular item. Most tourists
come to Shanghai for shopping and spend 1,090 yuan per person.
</P>
<P>
Some people complained about the inconvenient transportation,
expensive tickets at tourist spots, and rather ordinary souvenirs.
</P>
<P>
Experts consider Shanghai to be a good tourist market in the
Asia-Pacific region and one with great potential.  
</P>
</TEXT>
