<HEADLINE> France Beats Scotland 2-1 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 12 (Xinhua) -- France defeated Scotland 2-1 in
a soccer friendly match in St. Etienne on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have already secured their berths in the World Cup
finals with France as host and Scotland as the best second-placer
in the nine European groups.
</P>
<P>
After a number of opportunities squandered, France opened the
account with a pass by Lilian Thuram. As Scottish goalie Neil
Sullivan fell, Pierre Laigle surged ahead to kick home the first.
</P>
<P>
Within a minute, Scotland's Gordon Durie scored the equaliser
through two French defenders into the net.
</P>
<P>
After the break, France regained its upperhands in the 67th
minute when Laigle was roughly fouled. Youri Djorkaeff, who came
in the second half as a substitute, scored to make it 2-1.
</P>
<P>
It was the second victory in a row for France against a World
Cup bond team. France rallied to win over South Africa 2-1 last
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
